{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "AGCE Auth Service",
    "description": "Authentication & user management service for Arab Global Crypto Exchange.\n\n## Setup\n1. Import this collection AND the AGCE Local environment\n2. Select the **AGCE Local** environment in the top-right dropdown\n3. Run **Auth → Request OTP (Signup)** then **Auth → Signup (Email)**\n4. The signup response auto-saves `accessToken`, `refreshToken`, and `userId` to the environment\n5. Both Auth and KYC collections share these variables\n\n## Variables (in environment file)\n- `baseUrlAuth` — Auth service base URL (default `http://localhost:3000`)\n- `identifier` — email or phone under test\n- `password` — test password\n- `otp` — current OTP (dev OTP is always `123456`)\n- `jurisdiction` — INDIA / ABU_DHABI / DUBAI / GLOBAL\n- `accessToken`, `refreshToken`, `userId` — auto-populated",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check (Gateway)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Returns ok', () => {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('ok');",
                  "});",
                  "// Note: when accessed via the gateway, this returns the gateway's",
                  "// own health (service: 'agce-gateway'), not the auth-service's."
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrlAuth}}/healthz",
              "host": ["{{baseUrlAuth}}"],
              "path": ["healthz"]
            },
            "description": "Hits the **gateway** health endpoint (not the auth-service directly). This verifies the gateway is reachable. To check auth-service specifically, the gateway would need to expose `/healthz/auth` (not currently configured)."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Request OTP (Signup)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('OTP sent successfully', () => {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true;",
                  "});",
                  "console.log('Dev OTP is 123456. In production, check the SMS/email channel.');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"identifier\": \"{{identifier}}\",\n  \"purpose\": \"SIGNUP\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrlAuth}}/api/v1/auth/otp",
              "host": ["{{baseUrlAuth}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "otp"]
            },
            "description": "Generates a 6-digit OTP for signup verification.\n\nIn dev mode (`NODE_ENV != production`), the OTP is always **`123456`**. In production it's randomly generated and delivered via SMS/email."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Request OTP (Login)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('OTP sent', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"identifier\": \"{{identifier}}\",\n  \"purpose\": \"LOGIN\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrlAuth}}/api/v1/auth/otp",
              "host": ["{{baseUrlAuth}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "otp"]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Signup (Email)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Signup successful', () => {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(json.success).to.be.true;",
                  "  pm.expect(json.data).to.have.property('accessToken');",
                  "  pm.expect(json.data).to.have.property('refreshToken');",
                  "  pm.expect(json.data.user.isRegistered).to.be.true;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const data = pm.response.json().data;",
                  "  pm.environment.set('accessToken', data.accessToken);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('refreshToken', data.refreshToken);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('userId', data.userId);",
                  "  console.log('Saved accessToken, refreshToken, userId to environment');",
                  "  console.log('You can now run KYC requests with the same environment.');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"action\": \"signup\",\n  \"identifier\": \"{{identifier}}\",\n  \"otp\": \"{{otp}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\",\n  \"jurisdiction\": \"{{jurisdiction}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrlAuth}}/api/v1/auth",
              "host": ["{{baseUrlAuth}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth"]
            },
            "description": "Create a new user account using email.\n\n**Password rules:**\n- Min 8 chars\n- Not all numbers\n- Not all letters (case-sensitive)\n- Not equal to identifier\n\n**Required flow:**\n1. First call `Request OTP (Signup)`\n2. (Dev) OTP is `123456` automatically\n3. Run this request"
          },
          "response": []
        },
